@NODE "datasheet" "virtual_gc/datasheet (information)"


  NAME
      virtual.gadget -- a gadget for easy creation of GUI virtuals.

  SUPERCLASS
      gadgetclass

  DESCRIPTION
      virtual.gadget allows you to use groups that are much larger than
      the screen. The gadget acts as a window through which a rectangle
      area of its contents is visible.

  METHODS
      @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323}
      @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302}
      @{"GM_LAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 318}
      @{"DTM_PROCLAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/File" 288}
      @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}
      @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}
      @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}
      @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64}

      All other methods are passed to the layout.object passed in via
      @{"VIRTUALA_Contents" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 30}.

  ATTRIBUTES
      @{"VIRTUALA_Contents" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 30} (Object *)
          The gadget (probably a layout.gadget) to be displayed within
          the virtual.gadget. OM_SETing this attribute disposes the
          current contents of the gadget (if any).

          See also @{"VIRTUALA_NoDispose" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 69}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"VIRTUALA_NoDispose" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 69} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          By setting this attribute, you inform the virtual object that
          this child object should not be automatically disposed when
          the virtual object itself is disposed. This attribute allows
          sharing objects between layouts.

          Default is @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"VIRTUALA_Scroller" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 33} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          By clearing this attribute, you inform the virtual object that
          you don't want the vertical and horizontal scrollbar to be
          displayed.

          Default is @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"VIRTUALA_ScrollX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 36} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
      @{"VIRTUALA_ScrollY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 39} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
          Scroll the contents of the gadget either horizontally or
          vertically by the given amount of pixels. It's not possible
          to scroll the contents out of the view. Setting the attribute
          OM_NOTIFies the @{"VIRTUALA_TopX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 48}, @{"VIRTUALA_TopY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 51} tags.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, [@{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69}])

      @{"VIRTUALA_TotalX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 54} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
      @{"VIRTUALA_TotalY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 57} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
          The current/actual size of the objects' contents.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

      @{"VIRTUALA_VisibleX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 42} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
      @{"VIRTUALA_VisibleY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 45} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
          Get the visible portion of the contents.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

      @{"VIRTUALA_TopX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 48} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
      @{"VIRTUALA_TopY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 51} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
          Set/Get the current top value of the contents.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, OM_UDPATE, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

      @{"VIRTUALA_ScrollerX" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 60} (Object *)
      @{"VIRTUALA_ScrollerY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 63} (Object *)
          Instead of letting the gadget to allocate the scrollers,
          you can provide your own ones by using the tags above.
          virtual.gadget doesn't change their size and position.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63})

      @{"VIRTUALA_InputScroll" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/virtual.h/File" 66} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          By clearing this attribute, you inform the virtual object that
          you don't want the contents to be scrolled when the user moves
          the pointer out of the gadget while holding down the left
          mouse button.

          Default is @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

  BUGS
      virtual.gadget needs at least AmigaOS3.9 + BoingBag#1 (v45 classes).

  SEE ALSO
      layout.gadget/--datasheet--

@ENDNODE
@NODE "VIRTUAL_GetClass" "virtual_gc/VIRTUAL_GetClass()"
@{b}

  NAME@{ub}
      @{"VIRTUAL_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 29} -- Gets the pointer to the virtual class.@{b}

  SYNOPSIS@{ub}
      virtual_class = @{"VIRTUAL_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 29}();
      D0

      Class * @{"VIRTUAL_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 29}(@{"VOID" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 24});@{b}

  FUNCTION@{ub}
      Obtains the pointer to the virtual gadget class for use with
      @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}.  This function always returns a valid pointer so
      you do not need to check it.  The reason is that if the library
      opens fine, then the pointer returned is already setup.  (Of course
      this implies that if opening the library fails, you shouldn't be
      calling this.)

      Note that this function does not create the class, that is done
      when the class library is opened.@{b}

  INPUTS@{ub}
      Nothing.@{b}

  RESULT@{ub}
      virtual_class - Pointer to the virtual gadget class.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "RefreshVirtualGadget" "virtual_gc/RefreshVirtualGadget()"
@{b}

   NAME@{ub}
       @{"RefreshVirtualGadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 33} -- Refresh gadget in a virtual layout@{b}

   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       @{"RefreshVirtualGadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 33}(gad, virtual, win, req)
                            A0   A1       A2   A3

       void @{"RefreshVirtualGadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 33}(@{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *, Object *,
               @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *, @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} *)@{b}

   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Like @{"DoGadgetMethodA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/DoGadgetMethodA"}( gad, win, req, gpRender ), but ensures
       that proper clipping information is installed before invoking
       @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302}.@{b}

   INPUTS@{ub}
      gad = the gadget wanting refreshment.
      virtual = the virtual.gadget object containing the gadget.
      win = pointer to the window containing the gadget or its requester.
      req = pointer to a requester (ignored if gadget is not attached
         to a requester).@{b}

   RESULTS@{ub}
      NONE

@ENDNODE
@NODE "RethinkVirtualSize" "virtual_gc/RethinkVirtualSize()"
@{b}

   NAME@{ub}
       @{"RethinkVirtualSize" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 37} -- Calculate the size of virtual group based
               on the screen resolution.@{b}

   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       @{"RethinkVirtualSize" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 37}(virtual, rootlayout, font, screen, layoutlimits)
                          A0       A1          A2    A3      D0

       @{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91} @{"RethinkVirtualSize" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 37}(Object *, Object *, @{"struct TextFont" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/text.h/File" 89} *,
               @{"struct Screen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 133} *, @{"struct LayoutLimits" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 42} *)@{b}

   FUNCTION@{ub}
      This function is used to calculate the intial size of a layout
      group that contains a virtual.gadget (and ONLY one!). Simply
      call this function BEFORE you open the window:

      @{"RethinkVirtualSize" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/virtual.h/File" 37}(virtual, rootlayout, @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}, screen, &ll);

      This ensures that the visible portion of the virtual group will
      be as large as possible. Next open the window and set the window
      limits to values that were returned by the function in the
      @{"LayoutLimits" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/layout_gc/LayoutLimits"} structure you've passed in:

      @{"WindowLimits" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/WindowLimits"}( mywin, ll.MinWidth, ll.MinHeight,
                    ll.MaxWidth, ll.MaxHeight );

      Last but not least, set the new minimum size for the virtual.gadget,
      so that the user can resize the group:

      @{"SetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/SetAttrsA"}( layoutgroup_containg_virtual,
         @{"LAYOUT_ModifyChild" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 135}, virtual,
         @{"CHILD_MinWidth" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 246}, 64,
         @{"CHILD_MinHeight" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 251}, 48,
         @{"TAG_DONE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/tagitem.h/File" 39} );@{b}

   INPUTS@{ub}
      virtual = the virtual.gadget.
      rootlayout = the root layout.gadget of the window.
      font = optional pointer to the font used by the layout. May be @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.
      screen = pointer to the screen where the window will be opened.
      layoutlimits = optional pointer holding the actual minimum and maximum
       dimension of the window.@{b}

   RESULTS@{ub}
      If anything went wrong, this function returns @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98} (out of memory,
      @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} screen pointer, ...).@{b}

   BUGS@{ub}
      The function may become obsolete in a later release of ReAction.

@ENDNODE
